Parliament, Monday 7 June 2021 – The National Council of Provinces (NCOP) will tomorrow, Tuesday 8 June and Wednesday 9 June, hold virtual plenary sittings.
	
	The focus of the plenary sittings will be policy debates on Budget Vote. The Tuesday sitting will debate Budget Vote 16: Basic Education and Budget Vote17: Higher Education.
	
	DETAILS OF THE NCOP VIRTUAL PLENARY SITTING: 
	Date: Tuesday, 8 June 2021
	Time: 10:00
	Venue: Virtual platform
	
	The plenary sitting on Wednesday will debate Budget Vote 28: Police, Budget Vote 24: Independent Police Investigative Directorate, Budget Vote 21: Civilian Secretariat for the Police Service and Budget Vote 19: Social Development.
	
	DETAILS OF THE NCOP VIRTUAL PLENARY SITTING: 
	Date: Wednesday, 9 June 2021
	Time: 14:00
	Venue: Virtual platform
	
	Parliamentary meetings are open to the media and the public. Journalists who are interested in covering these meetings (including receiving links to virtual meetings) are requested to forward their contact details to Mlindi Mpindi on email mmpindi@parliament.gov.za for inclusion in the Parliamentary Communications Services WhatsApp Group, where such information is shared. Journalists must forward these requests using their official email addresses (no private emails).
	
	Members of the public may follow committee and House sittings live on Parliament TV (DSTV Channel 408), via live stream on Parliament’s YouTube channel and Twitter page on the links below. You may subscribe to the Parliament YouTube channel to receive instant notification of live feeds.
	
	Twitter: https://twitter.com/ParliamentofRSA
	Facebook: https://facebook.com/ParliamentofRSA
	YouTube: https://www.youtube.com/ParliamentofRSA
	
	ISSUED BY THE PARLIAMENTARY COMMUNICATION SERVICES
	Enquiries: Moloto Mothapo 082 370 6930 Parliament and its committees have the right to ask any institution or person to report to them and may summons any person to appear before them. Inkatha Freedom Party